#: ../../L/lost-in-the-underflow.rst:5
msgid "lost in the underflow"
msgstr "lost in the underflow"

#: ../../L/lost-in-the-underflow.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../L/lost-in-the-underflow.rst:9
msgid ""
"Too small to be worth considering; more specifically, small beyond the "
"limits of accuracy or measurement. This is a reference to floating "
"underflow, a condition that can occur when a floating-point arithmetic "
"processor tries to handle quantities smaller than its limit of magnitude. It"
" is also a pun on ‘undertow’ (a kind of fast, cold current that sometimes "
"runs just offshore and can be dangerous to swimmers). \"Well, sure, photon "
"pressure from the stadium lights alters the path of a thrown baseball, but "
"that effect gets lost in the underflow.\" Compare :ref:`epsilon`\\, "
":ref:`epsilon-squared`\\; see also :ref:`overflow-bit`\\."
msgstr ""
"考慮するに値しないほど小さい。より具体的には、精度や測定の限界を超えて小さい。これは浮動小数点アンダーフロー、すなわち浮動小数点演算プロセッサがその桁の限界より小さい量を扱おうとするときに起こりうる状態への言及である。これはまた‘undertow(引き波。岸のすぐ沖をときどき走り、泳ぐ者にとって危険なことのある、速く冷たい流れの一種)’をもじったしゃれでもある。「まあ確かに、スタジアムの照明からの光子の圧力は投げられた野球ボールの軌道を変えるが、その効果はアンダーフローに埋もれて消える。」\\"
" :ref:`epsilon`\\ 、\\ :ref:`epsilon-squared`\\ と比較せよ。\\ :ref:`overflow-"
"bit`\\ も参照。"
